- XXVIII. ARCHYTAS

Te maris et terroe numeroque carentis arenoe

HEE, measurer of the earth and of the main, And reckoner of the sands that know no score‚ Archytas 1 scanty heaps of sand restrain In hopeless bondage by Matinum’s shore. Nought it avails thee that thy restless mind Explored the starry chambers of the sky, And roamed the earth from pole to pole, —to find, At last, life's chief commission is to die.
